Um, ellipses to end sentences are very much a thing.  They show the editor omitted the end of a longer sentence.<br> <br>

That would be me -- the editor.  (There's only one ellipse in the original article, so if you're complaining about multiple sentence-ending ellipses, I'm the one to complain to.)  I trimmed a 6,500-word article into a Slashdot post.<br> <br>

That's going to require some ellipses.</div>
